From 37916d33fa882d51e14f665f753e6a50cd17e001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: reardonia <2925104+reardonia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 4 Jun 2026 22:52:20 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 5/7] Overlays: per-frame visibility signal, libass
 correctness, re-enable D2P detach

Replaces the always-on-once-libass-loaded HasOverlay signal with a per-frame
HasVisibleOverlay signal exposed through IPlayer, and rewires the consumers
that depend on it.

* OVERLAY::CRenderer: PrepareOverlays runs once per FrameMove on the render
  thread, calls ass_render_frame, caches the result on SElement, and
  MarkDirty's on actual change. Replaces the cross-thread MarkDirty
  formerly issued from CRenderer::AddOverlay on the video thread.
* OVERLAY::CRenderer::HasVisibleOverlay: per-frame visibility test that
  understands the libass persistent NOPTS container (presence in m_buffers
  is meaningless, the truth lives in e.renderedImages cached by
  PrepareOverlays).
* CDVDOverlayLibass: m_pendingChange OR-accumulates libass detect_change
  across frames so the consumer (ConvertLibass) sees the transition even
  when the walk runs one frame later than PrepareOverlays.
* IPlayer / CVideoPlayer / CApplicationPlayer: HasVisibleOverlay forwarder
  routes through the standard player abstraction (no DataCacheCore mirror).
* CRenderManager: m_renderedOverlay collapsed to m_renderedDebugOverlay;
  HasVisibleOverlay replaces HasOverlay in IsGuiLayer so IsRenderingGuiLayer
  downstream becomes per-frame accurate.
* CGUIWindowSlideShow: gate flipped from IsRenderingGuiLayer to
  !IsRenderingVideoLayer to express its actual intent ("keep walk firing
  when video flows through the walk"); independent of the per-frame signal
  rework.
* DRMAtomic: re-enable the detach-gui-plane optimisation that master
  shipped, with the gate corrected to include HasVisibleOverlay (so libass
  events don't blank). A @todo flags the layering violation of reaching
  WindowManager and CApplicationPlayer from inside the DRM layer; the
  follow-up refactor will parameterize FlipPage instead.
* OverlayRenderer.h: m_section is mutable so HasVisibleOverlay can be const.

Carries a temporary diagnostic log block in CApplication::Render
("[debug hack] count gui-on-screen frames vs total played and skipped") to
verify skip rate during draft testing; to be removed before merge.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
